-- Europa, PGE Shares May Be Active: Central European Equity Markets Preview
-- B y   M o n i k a   R o z l a l
-- 2010-10-10T12:55:25Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-10-10/europa-pge-shares-may-be-active-central-european-equity-markets-preview.html
The following is a list of companies
whose shares may have unusual price changes in central European
markets. Stock symbols are in parentheses after company names.
Share prices are from the last close.  Poland’s  WIG20 Index  fell 0.7 percent, the Czech  PX Index 
slid 0.4 percent and Hungary’s  BUX Index  lost 0.5 percent.  TU Europa SA  (ERP PW): The Polish insurer controlled by
Polish billionaire  Leszek Czarnecki  raised 239.4 million zloty
($84.2 million) from a sale of new shares. The offering was
combined with a sale of Europa shares owned by Getin Noble Bank,
which collected 238.7 million zloty for its 20 percent stake in
the insurer. Europa rose 2.3 percent to 188.7 zloty.  PGE SA  (PGE PW): The Polish government confirmed it sold 10
percent of the nation’s biggest power utility for about 4
billion zloty, which valued PGE shares at 21.3 zloty each.
Polish investors bought more than half of the PGE shares sold,
with domestic pension funds accounting for the largest share,
Treasury Ministry said. PGE dropped 1.3 percent to 21.31 zloty.  To contact the reporter on this story:
